Title: Creating a ToolTip Component in Blazor
Description:
In this blog post we will create a ToolTip component in Blazor from scratch. We will use the Blazor WebAssembly template to create a new project. We will then add a ToolTip component to the project and use it in the Index page. We will also add some styling to the ToolTip component.
The advantage over using a library is that we can customize the component to our needs as well as keeping it simple! So let's get started!

Title: Episode 119 - Comparers with Stephen Cleary
Description: Stephen Cleary, a renowned .NET developer and creator of the Comparers library, shares his knowledge of comparison, equality, and reference equality in .NET. During this insightful episode, Stephen explains the various tools available for developers to properly compare objects and create equality, such as the Spaceship Operator and the Comparers library. Stephen also takes a deep dive into the .NET Futures project, which explores potential future parts of the BCL. If you're looking learn more about .NET development, this podcast is a must-listen.
